HEADWORD: Zati
<hw>Za"ti</hw> <pr>(z⟦aum⟧"t⟦esl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A species of macaque (<spn>Macacus
pileatus</spn>) native of India and Ceylon. It has a crown of long erect
hair, and tuft of radiating hairs on the back of the head. Called also
<altname>capped macaque</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

